results.name: Number of divisors of n that are congruent to 0 modulo 10.
link: Reinhard Zumkeller, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000
formula: a(10k) = tau(k) = A000005(k); a(n) = 0 if 10 does not divide n. - _Franklin T. Adams-Watters_, Apr 15 2007
G.f.: Sum_{k>=1} x^(10*k)/(1 - x^(10*k)). - _Ilya Gutkovskiy_, Sep 11 2019
results.author: _Reinhard Zumkeller_, May 08 2003
